      "content": "It's completely understandable to feel uneasy with changes in your work environment, especially when they coincide with sensitive issues like an investigation into offshore accounts. While it's not necessarily cause for alarm, having increased responsibilities right after questioning certain matters could lead to feelings of being monitored more closely. It might be helpful to review your company's whistleblower policies and understand your protections before proceeding. Open communication with a trusted mentor or an HR representative would also provide clarity on your new role and peace of mind regarding your conduct.\n\nRemember, staying informed and seeking guidance from the right channels will help you navigate the situation with confidence. It's important not to jump to conclusions, but it's also okay to ask questions about how your role change aligns with your company's values and expectations.",
